  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A comprehensive 13-factor assessment was conducted; the assessment team concluded that the body of evidence, taken holistically, supports a Medium assurance level based on the breadth of validation activities, the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification campaign, and the conservative safety margins applied to all hemolysis thresholds. The decision record reflects acceptance of the simulation results for regulatory submission purposes. NOTE (adversarial): the declared assurance level of Medium is inconsistent with the structural evidence — the model form factor achievedLevel (2) remains below requiredLevel (4) at MRL 5, constituting a Critical gap (W-AR-02) that precludes any assurance level above Low under ASME V&V 40 rules.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-monte-carlo-uq-runs-5x5",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-grid-convergence-study"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-vr-bench-hemolysis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental dataset",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) compared against published FDA generic pump experimental data at 5 flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute error of 18% observed; systematic over-prediction at low-flow high-speed conditions attributed to model form limitations in the power-law hemolysis damage model. Despite the error magnitude, the assessment team judged predictions conservative and accepted results with safety factor application."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-vr-uq-monte-carlo",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "1000-sample Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainties (viscosity ±5%, pump speed ±1%, inlet flow ±3%) through the CFD surrogate. 95th-percentile hemolysis predictions remain below clinical threshold at all operating points. UQ campaign judged comprehensive by the assessment team and cited as primary evidence supporting the Medium assurance declaration."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-vr-grid-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Grid convergence index study — impeller and volute regions",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on impeller passage and volute. GCI values below 3% for velocity magnitude; GCI for wall shear stress (primary hemolysis driver) reached 9.8% on the finest mesh, marginally exceeding the 5% target. Discretization error assessed as controlled but not fully resolved at MRL 5 requirements."
    }
  ],
  "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4042689",
